init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They want to know why the other nations didn't honor their agreement.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The president of the United States, in response, declares war on the rest of the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The president then orders a nuclear strike on the rest of the world, but the missiles are intercepted by the rest of the world's forces.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The letter ends with the commander asking the president to join them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The president is welcomed with open arms by the people of the rest of the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The president is then taken to a banquet, where he is served the best food he has ever had.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He is not used to being happy.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The president of the world tells the president of the United States that he can stay as long as he likes.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He tells them to enjoy the peace.
